Avbob mutual assurance society has set aside R7 million for immediate assistance to communities of KwaZulu-Natal which have been severely affected by the floods in the province. The donation will be distributed in partnership with Gift of the Givers, Rise Against Hunger and the SPCA and include blankets, clothes, and food, reads a statement from Avbob. In addition, local Avbob branches will provide free funerals to a maximum of R20 000 per deceased, to help families bury their loves ones lost through the devastation. The MSC Foundation, the philanthropic arm of the Mediterranean Shipping Company and MSC Cruises, said it will donate R1 million to help communities affected by the floods in KwaZulu-Natal. The relief will be in the form of food parcels, blankets, and other necessities and will be distributed through reputable NGO’s in KZN. The MSC Orchestra and two MSC Cargo vessels that are currently sailing from Durban will also be donating water from the ships’ on-board water treatment plants. Mande Toubkin, general manager emergency, trauma, transplant and CSI at Netcare said in a press statement the Netcare Group is meanwhile calling for donations for a community relief project. Blankets, canned and other non-perishable foods, bottled water, sanitary products, nappies and warm clothing can be dropped off at any Netcare hospital, Netcare 911 base, Netcare Medicross, Netcare Prime Cure or Netcare Akeso facility.